# Summary

**Implicit Differentiation** involves differentiating both sides of an equation with respect to $x$ and solving
the resulting equation in terms of $y'$. Note $y$ is a function of $x$ so the [Chain Rule](chain_rule)
must be applied. One can also employ **logarithmic differentiation** by taking the natural log of both sides 
of an equation $y = f(x)$ and using the Laws of Logarithms to simplify. Afterwords, implicit differentiation is 
employed, and one can solve for $y'$.

